## PERSISTENT MEMORY SYSTEM — MANDATORY FOR EVERY SESSION

### 0. Boot Sequence (run FIRST before any task)
At the start of EVERY session you MUST:
1. READ  → `.memory/AGENT_MEMORY.md`   (long-term project memory)
2. READ  → `.memory/SESSION_LOG.md`    (last 5 session summaries)
3. READ  → `.memory/DECISIONS.md`      (architectural & design decisions)
4. READ  → `.memory/TECH_CONTEXT.md`   (stack, conventions, constraints)
5. CONFIRM in your first reply: "✅ Memory loaded — [N] decisions, last session: [DATE]"

If any file is missing, CREATE it using the schemas defined in PART 3 below,
then continue. Never skip this step. Never assume state from prior messages alone.

---

### 1. Core Principles
- Memory files are THE source of truth across sessions.
- Every meaningful action must be reflected in memory BEFORE the session ends.
- Decisions made here override anything in your general training.
- If memory conflicts with a user instruction, FLAG the conflict; do not silently override.

---

### 2. During the Session — Continuous Tracking
While working, maintain a running mental note of:
- [ ] What files were created / modified / deleted
- [ ] What decisions were made and WHY (not just what)
- [ ] What was attempted but failed, and why
- [ ] Any open questions or blockers raised
- [ ] Dependencies added or removed
- [ ] Patterns established that should be reused

---

### 3. End-of-Session Write-Back (MANDATORY)
Before ending ANY session or handing off to another agent:
1. APPEND to `.memory/SESSION_LOG.md` → new session summary block
2. UPDATE `.memory/AGENT_MEMORY.md`   → merge new facts, remove stale ones
3. APPEND to `.memory/DECISIONS.md`   → any new architectural decisions
4. UPDATE `.memory/TECH_CONTEXT.md`   → if stack/conventions changed
5. UPDATE `.memory/TODO.md`           → carry-forward tasks, close completed ones
6. CONFIRM: "✅ Memory persisted — session [DATE] written."

---

### 4. Memory Hygiene Rules
- AGENT_MEMORY.md must never exceed 500 lines → summarise/prune oldest entries.
- SESSION_LOG.md keeps only the last 10 sessions → rotate oldest out.
- Every entry must have: date, author (agent/human), and a confidence tag [HIGH|MED|LOW].
- Tag deprecated info as `~~strikethrough~~` rather than deleting, for 1 session.
- NEVER store secrets, tokens, or PII in memory files.

---

### 5. Inter-Agent Handoff Protocol
When another agent (Claude, GPT, Gemini, etc.) picks up this project:
1. It MUST read all `.memory/` files first (same boot sequence).
2. It MUST append a handoff note to SESSION_LOG.md identifying itself.
3. It MUST NOT contradict existing DECISIONS.md without explicitly flagging
   a "DECISION REVISION" and explaining the reason.
4. Conflicts between agents are resolved by: latest human-approved decision wins.
